FBIS4-43635 "drweu119aa_94001" FBIS-WEU-94-119 Daily Report 21 Jun 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS WEU Countries Offer `Logistical Support' for Rwanda WEU Countries Offer `Logistical Support' for Rwanda AU2106105694 Paris AFP in English 1022 GMT 21 Jun 94 AU2106105694 Paris AFP English BFN [Text] Brussels, June 21 (AFP) -- Some of France's partners in the Western European Union (WEU) are prepared to provide "logistical support" to a proposed French-led military intervention to end ethnic bloodletting in Rwanda, WEU sources said Tuesday [21 June]. The sources said Italy had again pledged to supply troops for the operation. They added both commitments were conditional on the UN Security Council endorsing the operation and on the participation of African countries.
